data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateAreaChartDescription
data.value:
Insert an area chart.
Area charts emphasize differences between several sets of data over a period of time.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateArea3DChartDescription
data.value: Display data as filled areas on a diagram, with each data point displayed as a peak or hollow in the area. Use it when you need to show trends for several series on the same diagram, and also show the relationship of the parts to the whole.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateFullStackedAreaChartDescription
data.value:
Display the trend of the percentage each value contributes over time or categories.
Use it to emphasize the trend in the proportion of each series.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateFullStackedArea3DChartDescription
data.value:
Display data as areas on a diagram, so that the value of each data point is stacked with all the other corresponding data points' values.
Use it for comparing the percentage values of several series for the same point arguments.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateFullStackedSplineAreaChartDescription
data.value: Behave similar to 100% Stacked Area, but plot a fitted curve through each data point in a series.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateFullStackedSplineArea3DChartDescription
data.value: Behave similar to 100% Stacked Area Chart in 3D, but plot a fitted curve through each data point in a series.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateSplineAreaChartDescription
data.value: Behave similar to Area Chart but plot a fitted curve through each data point in a series.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateSplineArea3DChartDescription
data.value: Behave similar to 3D Area Chart, but plot a fitted curve through each data point in a series.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateStackedAreaChartDescription
data.value:
Display the trend of the contribution of each value over time or categories.
Use it to emphasize the trend in the total across series for one category.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateStackedArea3DChartDescription
data.value: Display series as areas on a diagram, so that the value of each data point is aggregated with the underlying data points' values.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateStackedSplineAreaChartDescription
data.value: Behave similar to Stacked Area Chart but plot a fitted curve through each data point in a series.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateStackedSplineArea3DChartDescription
data.value: Behave similar to Stacked Area in 3D chart, but plot a fitted curve through each data point in a series.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateStepArea3DChartDescription
data.value: Show to what extent values have changed for different points in the same series.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateRangeAreaChartDescription

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateRangeArea3DChartDescription
data.value:
Display series as filled areas on a diagram, with two data points that define minimum and maximum limits.
Use it when you need to accentuate the delta between start and end values.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateStockChartDescription
data.value: Show variation in stock prices over the course of a day. The Open and Close prices are represented by left and right lines on each point, and the Low and High prices are represented by the bottom and top values of the vertical line which is shown at each point.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateCandleStickChartDescription
data.value: Show the variation in the price of stock over the course of a day. The Open and Close prices are represented by a filled rectangle, and the Low and High prices are represented by the bottom and top values of the vertical line which is shown at each point.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateFunnelChartDescription
data.value:
Display a wide area at the top, indicating the total points' value, while other areas are proportionally smaller.
Use it when it is necessary to represent stages in a sales process, show the amount of potential revenue for each stage, as well as identify potential problem areas in an organization's sales processes.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateFunnel3DChartDescription
data.value:
Display a wide area at the top, indicating the total points' value, while other areas are proportionally smaller.
Use it when it is necessary to represent stages in a sales process, show the amount of potential revenue for each stage, as well as identify potential problem areas in an organization's sales processes.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateGanttChartDescription
data.value: Track different activities during the time frame.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateSideBySideGanttChartDescription
data.value:
Display horizontal bars along the time axis. Each bar represents a separate event with the start and end values, hence these charts are used to track different activities during the time frame.
Use it when it's necessary to show activity bars from different series one above another, to compare their duration.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateLineChartDescription
data.value: Display trend overtime (dates, years) or ordered categories. Useful when there are many data points and the order is important.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateLine3DChartDescription
data.value: Display each row or column of data as a 3-D ribbon on three axes.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateFullStackedLineChartDescription

Consider using a 100% Stacked Area chart instead.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateFullStackedLine3DChartDescription
data.value: Display all series stacked and is useful when it is necessary to compare how much each series adds to the total aggregate value for specific arguments (as percents).

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateScatterLineChartDescription

data.value: Plot a fitted curve through each data point in a series.

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreateStackedLine3DChartDescription

data.name: ChartStringId.CmdCreatePointChartDescription
